 error(result, \"Error: \" + e.getMessage());\n        }\n\n        return result;\n    }\n\n    private void walkDir(Path root, Path current, String pattern, Boolean useRegex, \n                        Pattern regexPattern, List<Map<String, Object>> matches) \n            throws IOException {\n        try (var stream = Files.list(current)) {\n            for (Path entry : (List<Path>) stream.toList()) {\n                if (Files.isDirectory(entry)) {\n                    walkDir(root, entry, pattern, useRegex, regexPattern, matches);\n                } else if (Files.isRegularFile(entry)) {\n                    searchFile(root, entry, pattern, useRegex, regexPattern, matches);\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void searchFile(Path root, Path filePath, String pattern, Boolean useRegex,\n                           Pattern regexPattern, List<Map<String, Object>> matches) \n            throws IOException {\n        String relativePath = root.relativize(filePath).toString();\n        List<Map<String, Object>> lineMatches = new ArrayList<>();\n        \n        try (var lines = Files.lines(filePath)) {\n            int lineNum = 0;\n            for (String line : lines.toList()) {\n                lineNum++;\n                boolean found = useRegex \n                    ? regexPattern.matcher(line).find()\n                    : line.contains(pattern);\n                \n                if (found) {\n                    Map<String, Object> match = new HashMap<>();\n                    match.put(\"line_number\", lineNum);\n                    match.put(\"content\", line);\n                    lineMatches.add(match);\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        if (!lineMatches.isEmpty()) {\n            Map<String, Object> fileMatch = new HashMap<>();\n            fileMatch.put(\"file\", relativePath);\n            fileMatch.put(\"matches\", lineMatches);\n            fileMatch.put(\"match_count\", lineMatches.size());\n        